: Open the developer tools to show the page's markup. One simple wrapper div. No CSS/JS libraries.

* HTML

    <div id="site">
        <h1 ...
        <nav ...
        <main ...
        <aside ...
        <footer ...
    </div>

: Skip this slide in the presentation. It's here for people who don't see this live.

* CSS (part 1)

    nav {
      grid-area: nav;
    }
    h1.page-title {
      grid-area: head;
    }
    ...



* CSS (part 2)

    #site {
        height: 100%;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
        grid-gap: 1em;
        grid-template-areas: "head head"
                            "nav nav"
                            "main sidebar" 
                            "footer footer";
        }

